qas.question: The state hosts populations of birds of both endemic species and what?

context: The state is also a host to a large population of birds which include endemic species and <a0_0>migratory species<a0_0/>: greater roadrunner Geococcyx californianus, cactus wren Campylorhynchus brunneicapillus, Mexican jay Aphelocoma ultramarina, Steller's jay Cyanocitta stelleri, acorn woodpecker Melanerpes formicivorus, canyon towhee Pipilo fuscus, mourning dove Zenaida macroura, broad-billed <a1_0>hummingbird<a1_0/> Cynanthus latirostris, Montezuma quail Cyrtonyx montezumae, mountain trogon Trogon mexicanus, turkey vulture Cathartes aura, and <a2_0>golden eagle<a2_0/> Aquila chrysaetos. <a3_0>Trogon mexicanus<a3_0/> is an endemic species found in the mountains in Mexico; it is considered an endangered species[citation needed] and has symbolic significance to Mexicans.
